			</tr>
		</table> Tracking to '2' means that they are quartered. This increasing of Decay and Release rates at higher pitches imitates the natural response of acoustic instruments).</font></p>
		<center>
			<p><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><b>The Action Of Env1 &amp; Env2</b></font></p>
		</center>
		<p><font face="Arial,Helvetica">The tables below show that Env1 is modulating the pitch of DCO2 (the slave), so there's a rapid blip of sync sweep (and therefore a huge tonal blip) at the start of the note. T<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="2" frame align="right">
